Source: PexelsIf the town keeps on growing – population and economy – at the current rate and trend it can soon be recognised as a city. Forestry, farming and light industries along with tourism form the basis of the local economy. “All these can benefit from EP3 and its offerings,” the company said in a statement. EP3 Environmental (Pty) Ltd was established by Eben van Schalkwyk in 2013 and also has an office in Sandton, Johannesburg. “We are very excited with the prospect of settling and expanding our business in the Garden Route. Our vision has and always will be to provide high quality, affordable and value adding environmental and sustainability consulting services to our clients and to be recognised as leaders in the environmental and sustainability consulting sector,” van Schalkwyk said. Local SMEs get sustainable business support29 Mar 2022The company says its mission is to build long-term relationships with clients in order to support them to conduct their activities and services in a sustainable manner by considering and managing their social, economic and environmental aspects, ultimately achieving Business Sustainability. “With ever increasing pressure on organisations to conduct their activities and services in an environmentally sustainable manner, one can no longer ignore your social, economic and environmental aspects. At EP3, we advocate business sustainability where we consider and manage an organisations impact on the environment and the environmental impact on the business,” said van Schalkwyk.